chat_message.content:
For your computer vision project, you should use the **Image Object Detection API**. Here's why:

- **Image Object Detection API**:
  - **Description**: This API detects objects in an image provided through a URL and returns an updated image with bounding boxes around the detected objects. It also offers an option to return JSON metadata of the detections.
  - **Endpoint**: POST `https://api.example.com/v1/object-detection`
  - **Request Schema**: Requires `'image_url'` as a string (URL of the image to process) and optionally `'return_json'` as a boolean to give detection metadata.

The other APIs are not suited to your needs because:
- **OCR Text Extract API** is geared towards extracting readable text from images.
- **Vision Detect 3D API** is focused on 3D object detection using image sets, depth maps, or point clouds, not single images with 2D bounding boxes.

Therefore, the **Image Object Detection API** is the right fit for detecting and returning bounding boxes in your provided images.
